autofocus attribute.  https://t.co/5bOB0akGde When it loads it automagically focusses and onfocus it triggers   <input onblur=write(1) autofocus><input autofocus> First load input and set focus, then load new input and loose focus (onblur triggers)

<form id="test"></form><button form="test" formaction="javascript:alert(1)">X</button>  Button is set outside form, yet due to form= attribute still belongs to it. Javascript will execute as the action of the form.   <input onfocus=write(1) autofocus> Makes use of the
server and an Apache HTTP server.  Apache has released a fix for this vulnerability in Apache Tomcat 9.0.47, 8.5.65, and 7.0.109.

is installed by sending a specially crafted request.  This vulnerability is a result of an incorrect handling of chunked transfer encoding in the Apache Tomcat AJP Connector. The AJP Connector is a component in Apache Tomcat that is used to allow communication between the Tomcat

Modify a parameter value to include SQL code, such as "1' or 1=1--". If the system is vulnerable, this code may be executed by the database, allowing you to retrieve information or manipulate data.  Use tools such as SQLMap or sqlninja to automate the testing process.  2/2

Test for SQLi:  Add a single quote ('), semicolon (;), or double dash (--) to a parameter value. This can cause an error if the input is not properly sanitized, indicating that the system may be vulnerable to SQLi.  1/2
